## Cluster Architecture

### Overview
- **Type**: kubeadm-managed, bare-metal (Proxmox VMs)
- **Hypervisor**: Proxmox on node005 (Dell R620 — 56 cores, 128GB RAM)
- **Nodes**: 3 control plane + 1 worker (all 14 cores, 32GB RAM each)
- **CNI**: Calico
- **Container runtime**: containerd
- **DNS**: CoreDNS
- **No GPU**: GPU workloads run on ocean (Docker), not Kubernetes

### Node Map

| Node | IP | Role | VM ID |
|------|----|------|-------|
| kube501 | 192.168.1.51 | Control plane | 501 |
| kube502 | 192.168.1.52 | Control plane | 502 |
| kube503 | 192.168.1.53 | Control plane | 503 |
| kube511 | 192.168.1.61 | Worker | 511 |

### Network
- Flat subnet: 192.168.1.0/24
- Pod CIDR: (check `kubectl cluster-info dump | grep -i cidr`)
- Service CIDR: (check kubeadm-config)
- DNS: CoreDNS for cluster DNS, BIND on dns01 (192.168.1.2) for external
- No external ingress controller yet (services use NodePort or are internal-only)

